Depression does not discriminate. 
I REPEAT. 
It does not discriminate.

No amount of success, fame, money, kids, followers, likes matters. 

I pray for his wife. 
I pray for his children. 
I pray our mental health crisis…because it is a full blown crisis…changes. 
I pray that people think about the words they use or the actions they take towards someone before using or doing them.
I pray people choose kindness and if you can’t be kind, keep moving along.
I pray that social media stops glorifying perfect.
I pray that people understand everyone struggles and we all have our own battles we face. 
I pray we start to use our voices, we stop any shame or guilt or feeling like we need to hide if we are in a season of darkness.

This is so interesting to me. Did you know there are types?

Are you an introvert? 
Either self-titled or been labeled as one? What type fits you the best?

* Social Introvert:
Often thought as shy in social settings but that’s not always the truth. You just prefer to be alone at home or only go out with your select few of good friends rather than partying w/a large crowd of people. Being around people does not necessarily trigger your anxiety. You just like the comfort of being with yourself.

* Anxious Introvert:
They purposely isolate themselves to avoid the social spotlight, especially the unfamiliar ones. You feel awkward& painfully self-conscious around people as you may not be confident (or comfortable) with your social skills.

* Restrained Introvert: 
Restrained introverts prefer to “think before they speak”

* Thinking Introvert:
You are deep in your thoughts, wondering about life and analysing yourself. You don’t avoid social situations & don’t mind the presence of other people.

* The IDGAF AMBIVERT:
Both introvert & extrovert ... just a big ol’ mix of them all. Gives zero fcks about cliques, reads a persons energy. Values time with people who value yours, aren’t fake, doesn’t do drama, hatefulness or gossip. Likes to hang out in large groups but also values time to decompress and protects their PEACE at all costs. 

It’s meeeeeeee. IDGAF 🤷‍♀️🤣

My Christmas gift to myself this year? 
A commitment to my health, mind & body and loving myself fully & unapologetically...flaws and all.
.
I spent too much of my life obsessing over food. I spent soooo much time worrying about stretch marks, loose skin, mom belly jelly, cellulite & having a body that magazines and social media show as the “normal”. I spent so much damn time worrying about a number on scale or in a pair of jeans rather than how I truly felt on the inside. I thought a smooth belly, dimple free thighs and being skinny was perfect. I thought I had to see a certain number on the scale for me to feel confident.
.
I may have thought those things at one time but I’m so grateful I don’t anymore. I’ve learned how beautiful it is to be strong. I’ve learned how to appreciate myself just as I am. I’ve learned the number on a scale, the stretch marks on my skin, the cellulite on my thighs...that does not define my self worth nor my success on this journey to better health & on this health & fitness journey. I’ve learned it’s the non-scale victories that matter the most.
.
How did I get to this point? Flexible Nutrition. Convenient exercise that allows me to show up daily in some way for myself. An amazing community of women all working together each day in my Virtual Bootcamp and on my team to reach our goals, not just physically but in all areas of our lives.
.
And the biggest thing about this gift that I’ve given myself? Unlike new clothes, a piece of jewelry or some gadget that will eventually break, wear out or no longer be in style, it’s the gift that keeps on giving. It’s a priceless gift to my hubs. My kids. My friends. My team.

So when I share my heart, when you see me post my workouts or talk about things pertaining to this health & fitness journey I started on at 211+ lbs with high blood pressure & cholesterol, I want you to know it’s because it’s the greatest gift I’ve been given besides becoming a mom and a wife. I share this gift in hopes of showing other women that 1 decision can change your life.💕💯

It feels good to feel good.❤️
If you need someone to help support & encourage  you, I’m just a message away. 
Let’s get better together

When I see myself in photos, I no longer judge them by the way I look. Instead I connect to the smile on my face, joy in my eyes and peace in my spirit.💗

Regardless of wants, wishes, goals or it all requires action.  Not for 1 day, 1 week or 1 month. 

Daily consistent action.

Please do not confuse that with an all or nothing mentality or perfection. Because that’s what trips most people up. You are gung-ho about a new goal and super motivated so you go all in 110% … for 2 weeks…you can’t sustain it or you miss a few workouts, you eat like crap or you keep weighing yourself and you don’t see the number you think you should, based off the effort you’ve been giving. You give up.
.
Commit to NOT being that person.
It’s what you do MOST of the time that makes the biggest difference. It takes time but guess what? You have it. I promise it’s the journey and who you become in the process that matters. This is not a 30, 60, 90 day journey, it’s your LIFE.
.
Instead of going all in or nothing, choose a few habits that you can commit to and focus on implementing and once you have that down, add in a few more improved habits. This goes for any goal - health, relationship, spiritual, financial, business, etc…
.
I like to call it getting 1% better each day because that one percent better each day adds up to make the biggest difference over time.
.
.
Imagine there is a bank account that credits your account each morning with $86,400. It carries over no balance from day to day. Every evening the bank deletes whatever part of the balance you failed to used during the day. What would you do? Draw out every cent, of course? 

Each of us has such a bank, it's name is time. Every morning, it credits you 86,400 seconds. Every night it writes off at a lost, whatever of this you failed to invest to a good purpose. It carries over no balance. It allows no over draft. Each day it opens a new account for you. Each night it burns the remains of the day. If you fail to use the day's deposits, the loss is yours. There is no drawing against "tomorrow". 

You must live in the present on today's deposits. Invest it so as to get from it the utmost in health, happiness, and health. 
The clock is running. 
Make the most of today
It’s the first Monday of 2023.
Let’s get 1% better.

Carbs are not evil.
In fact, they are needed for energy.

Think about trying to run a car without gasoline; it’d be pretty hard, right? That’s basically what happens when you try to run your body without carbs - carbs contain glucose which is your body’s numero uno source for energy.

Here’s a kicker: it’s ok to eat white starches like rice, potatoes & pasta - in moderation of course. I actually found out awhile ago my body is highly reactive to brown rice & sweet potatoes but I can eat white rice and mashed potatoes like a boss - feel good and still get results. It’s crazy what happens when you learn your specific body and the foods it is reactive too, specific to you.

In 2023, throw the old and outdated beliefs out the door: carbs are bad, everyone should intermittent fast, don’t eat fruit, exercise for hours, eat 1200 calories or less, push your body hard every workout, no days off, blah blah blahhhh.

It’s linking arms with other women to make an impact in this world - whether through a laugh, a testimony, a helpful tip or just words of encouragement. 

I love being a woman and everything that goes along with it.

“A single mom, “shopping” in church pantries, living in section 8 apartments, having to decide between paying a utility, daycare or buying food. Upside down on car payments for years, having my truck repossessed all when my kiddos were babies.

Years later, once on my feet in the corporate world still trying to make ends meet, coaching came into my life.

Almost 10 years in, dream home built, kids college educations paid for, nest eggs & investments growing, family bucket list trips w/memories of a lifetime made & several cars paid for, here we are.

What changed for me was the moment I decided to stop watching everyone else take action on their dreams & goals and decided to take action on ours. Nothing would change unless something changed. 

It’s not about the material things.
It’s not calling “things” blessings, it’s about the freedom of time and finances this business allows, the moments like these with our kids, being able to be good stewards w/our finances & invest in things that matter most to us. I took action & yes I work hard but God continually shows up & shows out, meeting us where we are and providing exceedingly & abundantly.

I will never stop being grateful.
I’m not special, not lucky, I didn’t have any special training or experience, just a mom & wife who decided to say yes to an opportunity of a side home business & see where it took us.

So when I ask you what an extra $200-$500+ a month could do for you…When I ask how could starting your own side business, getting paid to get healthier & more fit and helping other people along the way help you? What can it do for your family? How can it change the trajectory of your life?”

#butbetter 

Salad:
1 package of Kale
4-5 apples diced
1 bag of matchstick carrots (optional)

Dressing:
1 cup of plain Greek Yogurt
3 Tbsp of Apple Cider Vinegar
1/2 C Mayo or Miracle Whip
 (MW if you prefer sweeter)
1/4 C raw honey
Salt & Pepper to taste

Directions:
Add bag of kale & diced apples to large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the honey + mayonnaise + apple cider vinegar + yogurt together and combine until mixed well. Sprinkle in salt and pepper to taste.
Pour the mixture over the kale and apples.
I put on disposable gloves and mix in the dressing to the kale leaves thoroughly by hand.
Store in a large Tupperware container with a lid and refrigerate for 3+ hours to get cold before eating.

10 minute family fav healthy recipe:
Air Fryer Sausage & Veggies

✨Ingredients:
1 red bell pepper - cut into 1 inch pieces
1 orange bell pepper – cut into 1-inch pieces
1 red onion – peeled and cut into 1-inch pieces
1 zucchini – cut into 1-inch pieces
1 tablespoon avocado oil
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder
1 teaspoon Italian seasoning 
1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
pinch of black pepper
1 package chicken sausage (12 oz) 

Directions:
Chop the veggies and add them to a large bowl.  Drizzle them with olive oil and toss to coat them all.  In a smaller bowl, mix the spices together with the salt and pepper and add the spice blend to the veggies.  Toss them in the spices to get them all nice and coated.
Slice the sausage into 3/4 inch rounds and add it to the bowl with the veggies and toss everything together.
Preheat the air fryer, if needed to 390 degrees F and spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray.  Add the veggies and sausage to the air fryer basket in an even layer and close and cook them for 10 minutes, flipping them in the basket halfway through the cooking time.  You may need to do this in batches depending on the size of your air fryer.

Once the chicken sausage and veggies are done cooking, remove them from the air fryer and serve as is or with cooked cauliflower rice or brown rice. 

Enjoy🫶

Glimmers are those micro moments in your day that make you feel joy, happiness, peace, calmness, or gratitude. 

➡️ Do you see/experience them? What are some glimmers you’ve seen or felt recently? 

Once you train your brain to be on the lookout for glimmers, the more these tiny moments will begin to appear.
.
 ✨Nervous System Ladder✨
You can become more in touch w/your nervous system and shift between different states or up and down the “ladder” as I like to refer to it. 

Top: Safe & Social [Parasympathetic State] 
This is the top of the ladder where you feel relaxed, calm, clearheaded, productive and able to connect w/others. This is when we experience joy, we’re present, compassionate and we have a sense that everything is OK. You have better digestion, immune response & circulation.

Middle:  Fight or flight [Sympathetic State]
This is where our body is tense, when we’re anxious, on edge, angry, scared, worried or we feel out of touch with others. Your blood pressure heart rate and adrenals & cortisol may be out of whack. 

Bottom: Shutdown [Dorsal Vagal Shutdown]
This is the state we’re in when we’re antisocial, withdrawn, foggy, numb, frozen or stuck, feeling trapped or disassociated. This is where we feel depression shame and hopelessness. 

It’s normal to shift between all 3 states of the nervous system - slight changes & even in big moments (most have enough resilience to bounce back to a regulated safe & social state.) But for some others, especially people who have experienced trauma or chronic stress, they get stuck here & getting back to the top of the ladder can be hard. But just like your brain can be rewired, so can your nervous system. It just takes work to form new habits + patterns.

One of the ways you can help reshape your system from fight or flight or shut down is being mindful of glimmers and paying attention to the experiences & interactions that help us feel safe, secure & settled. The more you practice this mindfulness + add it to your daily routine, the easier your nervous system will start to shift normally🫶

Having a regulated Nervous System positively effects your gut, hormones, energy, weight loss, digestion & immune system.

Halloween PSA: 
Don't be an asshat.

If a child comes to your door and grabs more than one piece of candy, don't be an asshat and say, "Hold up there, Mr. Greedypants!" Realize that, hey, this little one might just have fine motor challenges & you really need to get over the .37 cents you just lost in that moment. Instead, try saying, "Happy Halloween!"

If a child comes to your door without a costume on, don't be an asshat and say, "Really? No costume, no candy!" Realize that, hey, maybe this kid doesn't have the money for a costume or maybe this little one has sensory issues and can't handle that mask or that makeup. Instead, try saying, "Happy Halloween!"

If a child comes to your door & doesn't say Trick or Treat, don't be an asshat, maybe this child doesn't communicate through verbal speech. Maybe this little one uses sign language and you didn't see that or maybe this little one uses a communication device and his mom or dad is holding it for him. Instead, try saying, "Happy Halloween!"

If a child comes to your door & they look WAY too old to be trick or treating, don't be an asshat and say, "Aren't you a little old for this?" Realize that, hey, we all LOVE Halloween and that includes teenagers and everyone else. They are doing something fun & safe vs. getting into trouble somewhere. Instead, try saying, "I love Halloween too! Happy Halloween!"

If a child comes to your door & is on crutches, using a wheelchair, has a brace or a cast somewhere on their body, don't be an asshat and ask, "What happened to you?!" Realize that, hey, it's none of your business. Instead, try saying, "I love your costume! Happy Halloween!"
.

Halloween is one of the easiest holidays of the year. 
You buy candy. 
You stand at your door.
You answer the door. 
You smile & say Happy Halloween! 

That's it. That's all. 
Now go have a great day & celebrate Halloween...just don't be an asshat.
